In just an instant, it was all over.

Meteara was in the air, projected upward and away by the massive 
monster head. She was literally torn up where the fangs of the beast 
had bitten into her. Her stare was blanker than ever and was 
deteriorating at the second. It seemed as if time had stopped.

Meteara: Fi... rax... is...

She touched the ground and disturbed the dust and weeds under her. 
There, she died. Quietly, peacefully, but with a visible sense of 
regret as she had not even finished her mission.

A few meters away, Sanguine laid on the ground. Her materialization of 
the beast was now too hard for her to sustain. In fact, she could 
afford no energy to any transformation. She came back to the original 
little girl form, some of her artifices crumbling on the ground and 
liquifying in small pool of blood red nanites. She was hurt bad. There 
was still hope for her though. Her automatic warning beacon lit up and 
resounded on every Predacon frequency. She entered stasis lock.
